        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 6:21PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 621 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bluffton, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bluffton, Decatur, Berne, Ossian, Monroeville, Markle, Monroe,
Middletown, Middlebury, Preble, Nottingham, Willshire, Uniondale,
Wren, Poneto, Vera Cruz, Wellsburg, Murray, Liberty Center, and
Peterson.

This includes Interstate 69 in Indiana near mile marker 283.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
